article.headline: Central Florida 70, Stetson 66
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Marcus Johnson scored a career-high 18 points and Gary Johnson hit a pair of free throws with 3.7 seconds remaining to seal Central Florida's 70-66 win over Stetson on Tuesday night. The loss was Stetson's seventh straight to UCF (10-4, 3-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) and it was the Hatters third straight loss overall. E.J. Gordon's two free throws with 33 seconds left brought Stetson (4-9, 2-4) to 68-66. Gary Johnson then missed the front end of a one-and-one, giving the Hatters a chance to tie or take the lead, but Will Holloman's runner in the lane with 6 seconds to go fell short. Gary Johnson grabbed the rebound and was fouled to seal the win. Marcus Avant finished with 17 points and Gary Johnson and Josh Peppers added 14 points each for the Golden Knights, who were 6-of-9 from 3-point range in the second half and 12-of-25 for the game. Anthony Register kept Stetson in the game, scoring 14 of his 20 points in the second half. Karl Hollingsworth added 11 points for the Hatters.
